snippet: Queen Elizabeth has relinquished her role as patron of the All England Lawn Tennis Club (AELTC), home of the Wimbledon championships, after 64 years and will be replaced by The Duchess of Cambridge, a statement from the club said on Tuesday....
lead_paragraph: Queen Elizabeth has relinquished her role as patron of the All England Lawn Tennis Club (AELTC), home of the Wimbledon championships, after 64 years and will be replaced by The Duchess of Cambridge, a statement from the club said on Tuesday.

headline.main: Tennis: Queen Elizabeth Stands Down as All England Club Patron
headline.print_headline: Tennis: Queen Elizabeth Stands Down as All England Club Patron
